Adding Filters to the dashboard

We will use 3 page level filters on the dashboard to filter our data on. The Page Cnt, TotalSessionMin and User Sessions Group. 

Steps:

1.Double click on the slicer visual to select it

2. Click on the 'PageCnt ' column to select it. It will appear in the Field tab

3. To show 'All' options, click on the pointer and select 'Dropdown'


Adding the Total Session Min Slicer

Steps:

1.Double click on the slicer visual to select it

2. Click on the 'TotalSessionMin ' column to select it. It will appear in the Field tab

3. To show 'All' options, click on the pointer and select 'Dropdown'


Adding the User Session Group Slicer

Steps:

1.Double click on the slicer visual to select it

2. Click on the 'UserSessionsGroup ' column to select it. It will appear in the Field tab

3. To show 'All' options, click on the pointer and select 'Dropdown'


Filtering the dashboard with different slicers

To filter the dashboard with e.g. Pagecnt 2, click on the pointer and choose 2 and the scatter plot and map will be filtered accordingly.

Choose other options like 'Total SessionMin' 3 or 5 or combine different options of your slicers to get insights on the results.
